---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { site } from '@/config/site';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="SIG Round 4 — what farmers need to know before 30 September 2026"
  description="Slurry Infrastructure Grant Round 4 explained — £74m fund, eligible items, application timeline, and how WCCP supports SIG-ready precast deliveries before the 30 September 2026 deadline."
  schema="Article"
>
  <section class="bg-navy text-white">
    <div class="container-wccp py-14 md:py-16">
      <nav class="text-sm text-white/90 mb-6" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
        <a href="/news" class="hover:text-yellow">News</a><span class="mx-2 text-cast">/</span>
        <span class="text-white/90">SIG Round 4</span>
      </nav>
      <p class="eyebrow text-yellow mb-4">Industry update · 15 April 2026</p>
      <h1 class="font-display text-display-xl text-white mb-6 max-w-4xl">
        SIG Round 4 — what farmers need to know before 30 September 2026.
      </h1>
      <p class="text-white/85 text-lg max-w-3xl leading-relaxed">
        The Slurry Infrastructure Grant Round 4 is open — £74 million on the table, deadline
        30 September 2026. Here is what to look at first if you might apply.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-8 flex flex-wrap items-center gap-x-6 gap-y-2 text-sm text-white/90">
        <div>By <span class="text-white font-semibold">WCCP Engineering Team</span></div>
        <div>Published <time datetime="2026-04-15">15 April 2026</time></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <article class="container-wccp py-12 md:py-16">
    <div class="max-w-3xl">
      <h2 class="font-display text-3xl text-navy mb-4">What is SIG Round 4?</h2>
      <p class="text-cast-700 text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
        The Slurry Infrastructure Grant is a DEFRA capital grant for English livestock farmers to
        upgrade slurry storage and handling. Round 4, confirmed in early 2026, runs to a £74m
        fund with applications closing 30 September 2026. It funds new and replacement slurry
        stores, covers, agitation kit and slurry separators.
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-display text-3xl text-navy mb-4">Key eligibility points.</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-cast-700 text-lg mb-6">
        <li>Demonstrate at least 6 months' slurry storage capacity post-build, against your
          herd numbers (use the AHDB slurry calculator).</li>
        <li>Concrete stores designed and built to <a href="/standards-explained#ssafo-2018" class="text-ember underline">SSAFO 2018</a>,
          BS 5502-50 and BS EN 1992-3 with a minimum 20-year design life.</li>
        <li>Environment Agency notified at least 14 days before construction (form WQE1).</li>
        <li>Match-funding component — DEFRA contributes a share of eligible cost; the rest is
          on you or your bank.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="font-display text-3xl text-navy mb-4">The application timeline.</h2>
      <p class="text-cast-700 text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
        DEFRA usually invites Expressions of Interest, then full applications, with conditional
        offers issued in tranches. Build typically has to complete inside 12–18 months of offer.
        Don't leave the supplier conversation to the back of that window — concrete lead times
        compress as everyone hits the same deadline.
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-display text-3xl text-navy mb-4">How WCCP can help.</h2>
      <p class="text-cast-700 text-lg leading-relaxed mb-4">
        We have been casting <a href="/products/slurry-storage" class="text-ember underline">slurry
        storage panels</a> in North Devon for 55 years. For SIG Round 4 we are running a
        priority production schedule for grant-eligible jobs, with the paperwork pack already
        formatted to RPA expectations: structural calc, mix certificate, cube tests, declaration
        of performance, capacity statement.
      </p>
      <p class="text-cast-700 text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
        Read our full <a href="/grants/sig-round-4" class="text-ember underline">SIG Round 4 guide</a>
        for the deeper breakdown, or our pillar guide on
        <a href="/guides/slurry-wall-thickness" class="text-ember underline">slurry wall thickness</a>
        for the design detail.
      </p>

      <section class="bg-yellow/15 border-l-4 border-yellow p-6 rounded-r mb-10">
        <p class="font-bold text-navy mb-2">Deadline — 30 September 2026.</p>
        <p class="text-cast-700">If you might apply, talk to us before the summer. Q3 2026 will be the busy quarter and we are batching grant orders by the week.</p>
      </section>

      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
        <a href="/grants/sig-round-4" class="btn-primary">Read the SIG guide</a>
        <a href={`tel:${site.contact.phoneIntl}`} class="btn-yellow">Call {site.contact.phone}</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>

  <section class="bg-bone-200 py-12">
    <div class="container-wccp">
      <a href="/news" class="text-ember font-bold">← Back to news</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
